.TH SIMEIS 1 "2025" "simeis 0.1.3" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simeis \- multiplayer space exploration game server

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simeis-server

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simeis
is a multiplayer space exploration game server exposing a REST API on port 8080.
Players create an account, control a ship, explore the galaxy, trade resources
on station markets, and upgrade their crew and modules.

.SH USAGE
Start the server with the system service:
.PP
.RS
.B systemctl start simeis
.RE
.PP
Or run the binary directly:
.PP
.RS
.B simeis-server
.RE

.SH API
The REST API is available at http://localhost:8080 once the server is running.
Create a player with:
.PP
.RS
POST /player/new/{name}
.RE
.PP
The API key returned must be passed in the
.B Simeis-Key
HTTP header for all subsequent requests.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RUST_LOG
Controls log verbosity. Example: RUST_LOG=debug simeis-server

.SH AUTHOR
Timothee Cercueil
